    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-05-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="114"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-05-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 5, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 18.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to advise you that information
                    has reached me through a private source to the effect that within a week or two
                    the Colombian Government will send Gen. Marcellano Vargas, a sonin-law of
                    Vice-President Marroquín, to Washington, to negotiate for better or different
                    terms in connection with the Panama Canal convention.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. M. Beaupré.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
